📄 Step 2 — Business Rules & Relationships
👤 com.digitalbank.entity.Customer → com.digitalbank.entity.BankAccount

Rule:

One customer can have multiple bank accounts

Relationship:
com.digitalbank.entity.Customer (1) ─────── (∞) com.digitalbank.entity.BankAccount

Business rules:
A customer must exist before creating an account
Each account belongs to exactly one customer

🏦 com.digitalbank.entity.BankAccount → com.digitalbank.entity.Transaction
Rule:
One account can have many transactions
com.digitalbank.entity.BankAccount (1) ─────── (∞) com.digitalbank.entity.Transaction

Business rules:
Every transaction must belong to an account
Balance is affected only through transactions (important idea)

💳 Transfer Logic (VERY IMPORTANT)
Rule:
A transfer is ALWAYS:
1 WITHDRAW transaction (sender account)
1 DEPOSIT transaction (receiver account)
Link:
com.digitalbank.entity.Transaction.reference_id connects both rows

Example:

account_id	type	amount	reference_id
A	      WITHDRAW	 100	   TX-1
B	       DEPOSIT	 100	   TX-1
⚖️ Account Balance Rule
Rule:
Balance is NOT randomly updated.

👉 It is always based on transactions:

DEPOSIT → + balance
WITHDRAW → - balance

🚨 Important constraints
com.digitalbank.entity.BankAccount:
balance cannot go below 0 (optional rule for now)
com.digitalbank.entity.Status must be ACTIVE to allow transactions

com.digitalbank.entity.Transaction:
cannot exist without account_id
amount must be > 0
🧠 Final mental model
com.digitalbank.entity.Customer
   ↓ (owns)
com.digitalbank.entity.BankAccount
   ↓ (has)
com.digitalbank.entity.Transaction
   ↓ (linked via reference_id for transfers)
com.digitalbank.entity.Transaction

